Up to you, but maybe this should go in `Set/Image.lean` (as this file seems to only contain the simplest theorems about the operations). Then you could also prove it by chaining `preimage_image_eq` (in that file) and `mem_preimage`.

Also, maybe this should be a simp lemma?
Ah actually this lemma already existed in `Set/Image.lean` so I've removed my version.

```suggestion
theorem mem_lowerBounds_image_iff : f a ‚àà lowerBounds (f '' s) ‚Üî a ‚àà lowerBounds s :=
```

```suggestion
theorem map_isGreatest_iff_isLeast : IsGreatest (f '' s) (f a) ‚Üî IsLeast s a :=
```
I've heard its good (for readability) to include explicit args in the statements themselves. So maybe include `hf` manually in each of the statements? I am not fuzzed about it though.
